{{Flavour|This spell allows the caster to float in the air.}}

[[Levitation]] was a level 2 [[Charms]]/[[Air Magic]] spell which caused you to hover over the floor, ignoring all water or [[lava]] tiles and granting a bonus to [[stealth]]. However, it did have drawbacks: you became more vulnerable to the [[Airstrike]] spell, could not pick up items, and could not descend [[stairs]] until the effect has worn off. To avoid the last two of these, you could use the [[controlled flight]] intrinsic. You'd receive the [[fly]] condition instead, which had none of the down sides and a few extra perks.

Although this spell cannot be learned anymore, [[quaff]]ing a [[potion of levitation]] has the same effect.

==History==
The spell levitation was removed in [[0.10]]

